article.headline: Sam Houston St. 55, Stephen F.Austin 40
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Gilberto Clavell had 17 points and 11 rebounds as Sam Houston State avenged a 14-point loss to Stephen F. Austin earlier this season by beating the Lumberjacks 55-40 on Wednesday night. The Bearkats (16-12, 9-6 Southland), who lost to Stephen F. Austin 63-49 on Jan. 26, were 2 of 18 on 3-point attempts Wednesday and went to the free-throw line just twice, making one attempt. But overall they shot 52 percent from the floor and outrebounded the Lumberjacks 34-19. Stephen F. Austin (18-9, 9-6) was held to a season-low point total and shot 39.5 percent from the field, including 2 of 12 shooting on 3-point attempts. The Lumberjacks also didn't spend much time at the free-throw line, hitting 4 of 7 attempts. Jordan Glynn and Jereal Scott had 10 points each to lead Stephen F. Austin. Antuan Bootle also had 10 points for Sam Houston State, which won for the seventh time in its past nine games.
